-- Colombia Stock Movers: ETB Declines, Banco de Bogota Advances
-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 2012-01-02T21:20:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-02/colombia-stock-movers-etb-declines-banco-de-bogota-advances.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  rose 0.6 percent to 12,735.77, while the
Colcap Index rose 0.4 percent to 1,577.71. Colombian markets
were closed Dec. 30 for the year-end holiday.  Empresa de Telecomunicaciones de Bogota SA (ETB)  , the
phone company serving  Colombia ’s capital, fell 0.4 percent to
475 pesos. ETB, as the company is known, called for an
extraordinary shareholder’s meeting Jan. 11, according to a
 filing  on the regulator’s website.  Colombian banks saw profit rise 20 percent in the first
eleven months of the year to 4.12 trillion pesos ($2.1 billion)
from 3.43 trillion pesos a year earlier, according to data
released Dec. 29 by the financial regulator.  Banco de Bogota SA (BOGOTA)  , the nation’s second-biggest
lender, jumped 1.8 percent to 49,900 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Jaramillo in Bogota at 
 ajaramillo1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
